<br>
Its not once or twice, one someone makes typo's, the correct-spelling-trolls start to bombard the poor individual with remarks like learn how to spell you 11 year old kid! <br>
<br>
Well, people should learn how to spell obviously but remarks about peoples age is totally and utterly irrelevant. <br>
<br>
But ok, where's the catch ? Catch is that yes. We are not all American, nor British, Nor Australians or out of what ever nations that speak english as their main.. So whats up ? You think you can boost your ego's by pointing others mistakes or feeling a tad older yourselves while making other look like dribbling teen idiots?<br>
<br>
Take for example, me. Finnish school system teaches english from 3rd grade till 9. 3 more if you go to highschool and more in university. I didnt go to neither but i have 6 years of education and i've talked/written english (and yes, thats british english) since then so, that makes about 18 years now. And hell, i think i have quite a big vocab but still i make really really (and did i mention, really really really) stupid mistakes occasionally a) because im not a frigin translator and b) its not my frigin native tongue.<br>
<br>
So tell me, are you all turning into french now or what ?  (stereotype is that even they do know how to speak english, they wont)<br>
<br>
