<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=679780" target="top">My stuff</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=wolfaykin>Wolfaykin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Strength through Wounding</span><br>  Posts: 507<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/15/03 4:35 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3868.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Spelling and age. (or should be it speling?)</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>You think you can boost your ego's by pointing others mistakes or feeling a tad older yourselves while making other look like dribbling teen idiots?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
For those who speak english as a second language, it is one thing.  For those who speak english as a first language, I rarely point any mistakes out.<br>
<br>
But honestly.  There is a spell check button.  It will catch most mistakes.  And when communicating with the written word, people really need to realize that grammar, spelling, and use of the &quot;Enter&quot; key do make a first impression.  Just like pronounciation and grammar makes an impression in phone conversations, just like your appearance makes an impression in face to face meetings.<br>
<br>
When I point out grammar or spelling mistakes, it is normally because I gave up trying to read what they wrote, and missed their point, because it was too painful to struggle through.  People who make their entire post one HUGE paragraph are the biggest offenders here, but when every other word is mispelled or you have to spend 10 minutes trying to figure out what they mean because of grammar errors it is just as painful.<br>
<br>
If people care enough to express their thoughts and opinions here, and want others to take them seriously, they should at least try to present their point in a understandable manner.  A random spelling or grammar mistake is understandable.  We all make them, not one of us is perfect.  I don't think any of us are asking for a term paper quality proof reading job.<br>
<br>
But if someone can't be bothered to post their thoughts in a readable manner, then I can't be bothered to read it.  And out of concern that the post may have actually said something interesting, I will point out why I chose to not read it.<br>
<br>
*shrugs*<br>
<br>
People who point out every single little mistake and flame the person over them however, do need to get a bit of a life.<br>
<br>
