What annoys me is having to explain that no, I am not making spelling mistakes. I'm English. I resent calling my language British or U.K. English, too. I resent choosing U.K. English from the lists of languages in Microsoft programs and other computer products. It's not U.K. English... it's just English. The Americans are not speaking English. They are speaking U.S. English. I know it's petty, but it bugs me. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
